2":"1342–1402","1347–1411":"1347–1411","1336–1390":"1336–1390","1362–Female":"1362–Overleden","1365–1435":"1365–1435","–1347":"–1347","after 15 July 1347":"na 15 juli 1347","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1390":"1390","31 May 1407":"31 mei 1407","1435":"1435","1336":"1336","1347":"1347","1402":"1402","after 1339":"na 1339","1411":"1411","1365":"1365","1342":"1342","2 February 1390":"2 februari 1390","1407":"1407","Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala, Zweden","Älvsborg, Älvsborgs län, Norrbottens län, Sverige":"Älvsborg, Norrbotten, Zweden","Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Zweden"},"en":{"1340–31 May 1407":"1340–31 May 1407","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1342–1402":"1342–1402","1347–1411":"1347–1411","1336–1390":"1336–1390","1362–Female":"1362–Deceased","1365–1435":"1365–1435","–1347":"–1347","after 15 July 1347":"after 15 July 1347","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1390":"1390","31 May 1407":"31 May 1407","1435":"1435","1336":"1336","1347":"1347","1402":"1402","after 1339":"after 1339","1411":"1411","1365":"1365","1342":"1342","2 February 1390":"2 February 1390","1407":"1407","Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala, Sweden","Älvsborg, Älvsborgs län, Norrbottens län, Sverige":"Älvsborg, Norrbotten, Sweden","Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Sweden","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lama","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Carlos, Miguel, Jacobo, Jose Luis, Luis, Mario, Aleida, Beatriz, Catalina, Eduardo, Francisca, Gustavo.  Italian Luciano, Aldo, Antonio, Elio, Ezio, Guido, Nunzio, Salvatore.  Indian Amar, Basant, Hemant, Rakesh, Shyam, Sujay, Uday.","Nepali and Indian: Buddhist name from Tibetan <i>blama</i> ‘priest, monk’.","Spanish, Galician, Portuguese, and Italian: topographic name for someone who lived by a marsh, <i>lama</i> (from Latin <i>lama</i>), or a habitational name from any of numerous places called with this word."],"variants":[{"name":"Islam","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Arabic/Muslim Mohammed, Mohammad, Nurul, Rafiqul, Nazrul, Muhammad, Shahidul, Saiful, Shafiqul, Kazi, Mohamed, Syed.","Muslim: from a personal name based on Arabic <i>islām</i> ‘peace’, the Arabic name of the religion of Muslims. <i>Islām</i> is mentioned in several places in the Koran, for example at 3:19 ‘Religion with Allah is Islām (peace)’ and 5:3 ‘I have chosen for you Islām (peace) as religion’. This name is often found in combinations, e.g. <i>Nūr al-Islām</i> ‘light of Islam’.","Turkish (<b>İslam</b>): ornamental name from <i>İslam</i> ‘Islam; Muslim’."]},{"name":"Lami","meanings":["Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Lama  .","French (also <b>L'Ami</b>): variant of   Lamy  .","Muslim (Iraq and Maghreb): from a personal name based on Arabic <i>lāmiʿ</i> ‘sparkling, shiny’."]},{"name":"Lalama","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Domenic, Attilio, Donato, Ettore, Gino, Giuseppe, Maddalena, Marcello, Remo.  Spanish Angel, Aida, Carlos, Elena, Jorge, Luis.","Italian (<b>La Lama</b>) and Spanish: variant of   Lama  , with the definite article <i>la</i>. This surname is very rare in Italy (found in Foggia province, Apulia)."]}]},{"name":"Filip","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek <i>Philippos</i> (‘love’ + ‘horses’).  See  <b>Philip</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Philip","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."]}]},{"name":"Karlsson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Lars, Anders, Alf, Bjorn, Erik, Kerstin, Agust, Elnar, Fritjof, Gudmundur, Johan, Kristinn.","Swedish: patronymic from the personal name   Karl   (see also   Charles  ). Compare   Carlsson  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Karlson","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Algot, Lars, Nils, Eskil, Holger, Knute, Lennart, Sven.  German Kurt, Hans, Otto.","Americanized form (and a very rare Swedish variant) of Swedish   Karlsson  .","Americanized form of Norwegian and Danish   Karlsen  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Karl","meanings":["equivalent of   Charles  , also used in the English-speaking world.  See also  Carl ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1357050,"age":10,"year":"1350","julianDay":2214138,"description":"Black Death killed one-third of population.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Filip Karlsson Folkunga Lama was born in 1340, in Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Sweden as the son of Karl Magnusson and Cecilia Birgersdotter. He married Ingeborg Kettilvasta Dotter on 2 February 1390. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 31 May 1407, at the age of 67, and was buried in Uppsala, Sweden."},"et":{"1340–31 May 1407":"1340–31. mai 1407","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1342–1402":"1342–1402","1347–1411":"1347–1411","1336–1390":"1336–1390","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1365–1435":"1365–1435","–1347":"–1347","after 15 July 1347":"pärast 15. juulit 1347","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1350":"1350","1390":"1390","31 May 1407":"31. mai 1407","1435":"1435","1336":"1336","1347":"1347","1402":"1402","after 1339":"pärast 1339","1411":"1411","1365":"1365","1342":"1342","2 February 1390":"2. veebruar 1390","1407":"1407","Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala, Rootsi","Älvsborg, Älvsborgs län, Norrbottens län, Sverige":"Älvsborg, Norrbotten, Rootsi","Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Sweden":"Uppsala-Näs, Uppsala, Rootsi"},"fi":{"1340–31 May 1407":"1340–31. toukokuuta 1407","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1342–1402":"134